title: The Speeches of the five Jesuits that were executed at Tyburn on Friday the 20th of this instant June, 1679
author: Whitbread, Thomas, 1618-1679.
notes: Includes the speeches of Thomas Whitebread, William Barrow (alias Harecourt), John Caldwell (alias Fenwick), and John Gavan; Turner's speech was omitted as too long.
Reproduction of original in the Huntington Library.
